sic questions about the library  Course Reserves Circulation staff also maintain the Course Reserves collection  This includes print  audio visual  and electronic materials  selected by faculty for use in their classes  Interlibrary Loan Interlibrary Loan staff borrow materials from other libraries when cadets  faculty  and staff need items which Preston Library does not own  There are no limits and no fees for this service  Requested materials may take one day to two weeks or more to arrive  To initiate a request  log in to the Interlibrary Loan system    Col  Susan Hastings Ms Tonya Moore  Head  Access Services Interlibrary Loan Manager hastingssf vmi edu mooretl vmi edu 464 7607 464 7570      Ms Alicia Wheeler Ms  Gwen Sichol Circulation Assistant Circulation ILL Assistant wheeleras vmi edu   sicholgb vmi edu 464 7129 464 7757 VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 